      "content": "\"Observe their customs, gentlemen; they are steeped in a savage simplicity, their lives governed by instinct rather than reason. Their adherence to mere tribal custom, devoid of true law or sophisticated governance, leaves them vulnerable to their own brutish impulses. We must impose the discipline of the Crown, for without the firm hand of European morality, these peoples will forever remain mired in a state of barbarism.\"",
      "source": "target",
